commit.message: Recognize .cc as having C++-style comments

Fix bug on Windows where ${CHECKFILE_ABS_PATH} was used inside a regex.
When this happened on Windows we would substitute in a path containing
"\" which would be interpreted as a regex escape which would break
parsing of the regex.

Switched to using a different method for generating the script used as a
entry point into the tool.

The previous method works fine on Linux but on Windows we get a script
that cannot be executed directly from the command line (we have to
prepend the python executable). This new method generates an entry point
script on Linux and on windows it actually generates a .exe file as
entry point so the tool can be run directly from the command line :)

I've switched from distutils.core to setuptools to squash the warning I
was getting about entry_points being ignored. Despite that it was still
working correctly on distutils.

Note I've still kept bin/OutputCheck because the testing framework still
depends on it and its nice to have a script I can run directly in the
repo.

Properly fix packaging problem for Python3. On download via pip
we would fail because str has no .decode() method.

Fix packaging problem where git tag was parsed but we got bytes
back so setup.py script would create wrong name for PyPi package.

Document ${...} substitutions

The documentation could be a little better here...
Fix rendering issues of README.md on GitHub

Document literal string CHECK directives

The documentation could be better, but I'm feeling lazy.

Added support for ${LINE}, ${LINE:+N} and ${LINE:-N} substitutions in
directives. A newly added flag --disable-substitutions can disable this
behaviour.

Added test cases for mixing CHECK-NOT: and CHECK-NOT-L:

Although it might be desirable we can't support this right now
because internally we try to merge adjacent NOT directives together.

This doesn't work here. We would need some sort of promotion where
CHECK-NOT-L: directives get promoted to CHECK-NOT: directives...
this would be a pain to do. User's can easily work around this by
just using CHECK-NOT or CHECK-NOT-L exclusively in a region.

Add test to check that having a CHECK-NEXT: following a CHECK-NOT-L:
is considered invalid.
Added basic support for CHECK-NOT-L: directive.
Refactor CheckNot directive.

Remove redundant directive validation rule and add test to check
that using a check-next-lit after a check-not is invalid.

Directive validation now allows a CHECK-NEXT-L: directive before
a CHECK-NEXT: directive.
Add basic support for CHECK-NEXT-L: directive
Added support for CHECK-L in existing validation rules.

Refactor validation of Directives list so it lives in the parser.
This seems cleaner.
Added basic implementation of CheckLiteral.

If python executable specified by --param=python_exec=<PYTHON>
is not in PATH then abort testing.

Fix bug for python2 when parsing the CHECK directives in a file with
dos line endings. The extra line ending character would become
part of the regex pattern which would mean it wouldn't match
anything!

Added --param=python_exec=<path to python> option to lit tests so
we can easily change python interpreter

Fix bug where files containing Windows line endings were not handled
correctly. This also removes '\n' from the end of the lines when
doing comparisions.

Added --dump-input-file command line option to show input (useful for
pipes) to OutputCheck. A test case for this option has been added.

Fix bug in OutputCheck program that calls driver. If OutputCheck is
installed by pip then when we run the test suite the installed version
gets used rather than the git repo version because the system import
is attempted and only if that failed would we look in the git repo
for the OuputCheck package.

Now we do it the other way round so if OutputCheck if being run from
the Git repository we use that in preference to a system installed
version.
Added support for Microsoft Boogie files.
Alphabetically ordered comment prefixes.

lit 0.3.0 (from LLVM3.5SVN) is now available in PyPi.
Teach travis to use it instead of using our own git mirror.

Fixed bug where the --file-to-check command line argument could
not be parsed. A test case has been added for this bug.
